I think people are taking this WAYYYYY out of proportion! Jennifer the person just used that as an example NOT a comparison.. She was just saying no one knows who their child is going to turn out to be when they get here.. Personally I think everyone should be respectful and accepting to everyone within reason, but just because you accept/care for someone doesn't mean you accept all of their choices, and it doesn't mean you don't love them any less because of it. with transgender and homosexual children I'm sure all were aware of the possibility yet didn't expect them to be that way, but they still love them deep down whether or not they agree with their child's sexuality.
